                                                                    <div class="moto-widget-text-content moto-widget-text-editable">
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“Now may the God of peace Himself sanctify you completely; and may your whole spirit, soul, and body be preserved blameless at the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ. He who calls you is faithful, who also will do it.”
                                                                            <b>I Thessalonians 5:23-24 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“No temptation has overtaken you except such as is common to man; but God is faithful, who will not allow you to be tempted beyond what you are able, but with the temptation will also make the way of escape, that you may be able to bear it.”
                                                                            <b>I Corinthians 10:13 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">God is faithful and can be unfaithful in no way.  God’s faithfulness is who He is and all that He ever was and all that He ever will be, just as we see in His immutability.  He changes not!  This gives us great security and peace.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">I keep as a reminder as we are seeking to expand our perspective on who is the God we serve, who makes Himself so available to us as we journey through each attribute we must continue to see how each attribute again is intertwined with the others and it must always stay balanced.  To have one appear more prominent would cause God to be less than perfect.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">The word tells us nothing is impossible with God.  It is impossible for God to be anything less then who His attributes attest Him to be and this is true for faithfulness being who God is.  God will always be true to Himself.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">As <b> I Corinthians 10:13</b> tells us that all temptations common to man are overseen by God.  Nothing can influence us with out His knowledge as He is Omniscient.  He is faithful to not allow the temptation more than we can handle giving us the way of escape which is not always an easy route.  The way of escape will cost us two choices. First the cost not to fall for the temptation, second the choice to take the way of escape.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">A little boy was in the candy store and as the clerk observed his behavior he said, “son it looks to me that trying to steal yourself some candy.” The little boy replied, “No sir I’m trying NOT to steal myself some candy.” He made the first choice but taking the way of escape needs strength of a different kind.  This requires depending on God’s grace.  God’s grace gives us the strength to see the temptation for what it is, and bear it .
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">One of my favorite scriptures is 1 John 1: 9, “If we confess our sin He is faithful and just to forgive us our sins and cleanse us from all unrighteousness.”
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">There are times we take our eyes off Jesus and fall into temptation.  And we see our Father offers yet another way out.  If we confess our sin...He is willing to forgive us and able to cleanse us from unrighteousness.  We serve a faithful God.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">All part of making us complete in spirit, soul and body to be presented blameless at the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ .
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Father forgive our unbelief and help us to trust You are who You say You are.  We have no reason to doubt You.  Let doubt not hinder us from receiving Your faithfulness in our lives.  That by our doubt we might not hinder You.  Let us trust You with child like faith.  You are faithful and true ABBA.  We are grateful.  Amen
                                                                        </p>
